Hosts and distribution . Five species are ectoparasites of African Estrildidae ( Passeriformes ) (
Gaud 1968
). One species (
O . nidicola
) was collected from nests of
Passer domesticus Linnaeus
( Passeridae ) in Brazil (
Fain & Rosa 1971
). This is probably also a parasitic species whose specimens (
2 females
) happened to have fallen off the body of the host and into the nest. The record of
O . spinitarsis
(
Fain and Gaud, 1984
)
from a museum specimen of
Pogoniulus scolopaceus (Bonaparte)
( Piciformes : Lybiidae ) originating from D.R. of the Congo (
Fain & Gaud 1984
) needs confirmation.
